``id``
 to 
``sys users``
 (#17577)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17563] updated how 
``$NU_LIB_DIRS``
 / 
``$env.NU_LIB_DIRS``
 is handled at startup time (#17563)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17558] abstracted env var names so they're insensitive on windows and sensitive on other operating systems (#17558)
@astral-l:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17589] used RFC 3339 formatting for displaying dates with year > 9999 (#17589)
@amaanq:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17581] fixed: used write_all instead of eprintln! to avoid double-panic on stderr teardown (#17581)
@WindSoilder:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17571] pipefail: fixed freeze when assigning a large result of an external command to a variable (#17571)
@hustcer:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17568] attempted to fix "TLS required, but transport is unsecured" error (#17568)
@it-education-md:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17525] fixed pipeline 
``let``
 builtin var validation (#17525)
@cablehead:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17507] allowed Ctrl+C to interrupt HTTP requests (#17507)
@app/dependabot:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17587] built(deps): bumped uuid from 1.20.0 to 1.21.0 (#17587)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17582] built(deps): bumped crate-ci/typos from 1.43.4 to 1.43.5 (#17582)
